1. write md code to create a gallery - only the above one md file to contain all the images given below
2. convert below html to hugo html that will consume the gallery given in the md file
3. write js for fancybox and loazyload images 

<div id="gallery-grid" class="gallery-grid">

<a class="gallery-item" href="" data-fancybox="gallery" aria-label="" title="Live Concert 2">
<img src="" alt="">
</a>
</div>

scss
.gallery-grid {
	column-count: 3;
	column-gap: 15px;
	max-width: 1200px;
	margin: 0 auto;

	.gallery-item {
		display: inline-block;
		width: 100%;
		margin-bottom: 15px;
		position: relative;
		overflow: hidden;
		border-radius: 10px;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: transform 0.3s ease-in-out, box-shadow 0.3s ease-in-out;

		&:hover {
			transform: scale(1.05);
			box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
		}

		img {
			width: 100%;
			border-radius: 10px;
			transition: 0.3s ease-in-out;
		}
	}
}

// Responsive Masonry Grid
@media (max-width: 1024px) {
	.gallery-grid {
		column-count: 2;
	}
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
	.gallery-grid {
		column-count: 1;
	}
}


